#5905
Farret's Last Cry.~
You stand in a large open arena. Large pillars stand upright like 
silent guardians of death. Huge grandstands stand unoccupied and seem 
ghostlike. The air smells of death. The air is cold as it blows a chill
breeze by your face. Dust swirls on the ground and ghostly voices seem to
fill your ears. Then you hear a silent cry... the cry of death and look
over and see a ghost of a young elf falling in a death cry. Another ghost
stands over him in silent victory...He looks at you and cackles gleefully.
He raises his hand and says, " Victory is mine at last! Farret is gone...
The greatest of pkillers in all the realms has at last fallen!" Then a
ghostly lightning bolt arcs through the air and strikes the ghost in the
chest and suddenly everything vanishes...the air is quiet again. You are
left alone in the wind awaiting combat...Victory could be yours!
~
